        <field>SetupGuidanceMarkdown__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">## Google Chat setup

### One-time setup per space

1. In Google Chat, open the target space -&gt; space name dropdown -&gt; **Apps &amp; integrations**
2. **Add webhooks** -&gt; **Add another webhook**
3. Name the webhook (any label) and optionally add an avatar image URL
4. Copy the webhook URL Google shows you (starts with `https://chat.googleapis.com/v1/spaces/...`)

### Salesforce setup

- Paste the webhook URL into this service&apos;s `Webhook URL` field
- Named Credential mode is technically supported but rarely useful - Google Chat webhooks include a signed key in the URL itself, so there&apos;s no additional auth to wrap.

### Message format

The notifier sends Google Chat&apos;s `text` and `cardsV2` payload shape. Rich formatting (bold, links, code blocks) uses Google Chat&apos;s own Markdown-like syntax, which differs from Slack&apos;s.</value>
